ball in the air.

01:31.600 --> 01:36.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, this generation hitters
is all about launching
the ball in the air and
not necessarily hitting

01:40.700 --> 01:42.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
it on the ground
for batting average.

01:42.066 --> 01:44.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It more about in
the air or slugging.

01:44.233 --> 01:46.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So, speaking of
this generation, we have these
two new rookie stars, and they

01:46.766 --> 01:49.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
happen to be in very
large markets, right,
New York and L.A.

01:49.866 --> 01:52.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
