there has been a
long learning curve.

02:08.000 --> 02:11.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Even when they get to
the Major Leagues, after
their apprenticeship
in the minor leagues,

02:11.500 --> 02:15.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it takes a while for a
player to establish himself.

02:15.400 --> 02:19.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What we're seeing now in
recent years -- and Judge and
Bellinger are great examples of

02:19.700 --> 02:24.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
this -- hitters becoming impact
players almost immediately as
soon as they get to the big

02:25.166 --> 02:26.800 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
leagues.

02:26.800 --> 02:28.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Now, I think this has
something to do with
our society in general.

02:28.266 --> 02:31.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We're now specializing
at early ages.

02:31.333 --> 02:36.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, these hitters now
are specializing on the
art of hitting, rather
than playing multiple

02:37.700 --> 02:40.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
sports, locking in on
their specific skills.

02:40.766 --> 02:44.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, Judge and Bellinger
have hit the ground running.

02:44.600 --> 02:46.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And one more thing.

02:46.666 --> 02:51.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
